    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`helpers.exec` with `echo` never completes sometimes if message width is greater than screen width.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create `test/functional/issue_spec.lua`:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal helpers = require('test.functional.helpers')(after_each)\r\nlocal Screen = require('test.functional.ui.screen')\r\n\r\nbefore_each(helpers.clear)\r\n\r\ndescribe(\"echo 11 chars\", function()\r\n  it('with screen width = 20', function()\r\n    Screen.new(20, 5):attach()\r\n    helpers.exec([=[echo \"12345678901\"]=])\r\n  end)\r\n  it('with screen width = 10', function()  -- this works fine\r\n    Screen.new(10, 5):attach()\r\n    helpers.exec([=[echo \"12345678901\"]=])\r\n  end)\r\nend)\r\n\r\ndescribe(\"echo 12 chars\", function()\r\n  it('with screen width = 20', function()\r\n    Screen.new(20, 5):attach()\r\n    helpers.exec([=[echo \"123456789012\"]=])\r\n  end)\r\n  it('with screen width = 10', function()  -- this does not complete\r\n    Screen.new(10, 5):attach()\r\n    helpers.exec([=[echo \"123456789012\"]=])\r\n  end)\r\nend)\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Run functional tests:\r\n```sh\r\nTEST_FILE='test/functional/issue_spec.lua' make functionaltest\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Result (after 20 minutes):\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/65824523/56dd380c-66cd-4d95-b763-169a661e5570)\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTest #‚Äç4 (12 chars with screen width 10) should pass.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-ba0370b1d-dirty\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWSL Ubuntu 22.04.2 LTS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n?\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": "2024-02-21T20:58:12Z",
